00:23:26,978 --> 00:23:28,735
Do I feel guilty? Yes.

514
00:23:28,793 --> 00:23:31,380
Fortunately, that's what
this place was made for.

515
00:23:34,662 --> 00:23:36,695
At least Weevil was right
about one thing.

516
00:23:36,923 --> 00:23:41,143
Fr. Patrick Fitzpatrick does look
rather unecclesiastical.

517
00:23:41,377 --> 00:23:44,740
Definitely the priest I want
on my side in a team knife fight.

518
00:24:05,447 --> 00:24:09,233
I'm really sorry about this.

519
00:24:23,289 --> 00:24:24,288
I'm going to hell.

520
00:24:25,043 --> 00:24:26,087
It's that simple.

521
00:24:26,088 --> 00:24:28,313
I am going straight to hell.

522
00:24:28,534 --> 00:24:30,888
Confession hasn't quite started yet,

523
00:24:31,066 --> 00:24:32,432
but what makes you say that?

524
00:24:33,942 --> 00:24:35,965
Um...well,

525
00:24:37,003 --> 00:24:40,646
I've done some things
that probably aren't quite,

526
00:24:41,182 --> 00:24:41,796
you know,

527
00:24:43,007 --> 00:24:44,007
on the up-and-up,

528
00:24:44,859 --> 00:24:45,837
god-wise.

529
00:24:45,838 --> 00:24:48,916
I see. Is there an example of this?

530
00:24:49,457 --> 00:24:51,993
Sometimes, when I know someone is bad,

531
00:24:51,994 --> 00:24:54,893
I do improper things.

532
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,339
Like what?

533
00:24:57,883 --> 00:24:58,982
Like...

534
00:24:59,827 --> 00:25:03,529
trying to prove to the world that
they're bad and get them punished.

535
00:25:04,246 --> 00:25:07,344
Yes, I know the feeling,
actually.

536
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:08,596
You do?

537
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:09,683
I wasn't always...

538
00:25:10,432 --> 00:25:12,970
on the up-and-up god-wise myself,

539
00:25:13,673 --> 00:25:14,607
but I worked at it.

540
00:25:15,696 --> 00:25:19,376
There's a passage --
Romans 12:19.

541
00:25:20,285 --> 00:25:21,794
"Vengeance is mine.

542
00:25:22,484 --> 00:25:24,725
I will repay, sayeth the lord."

543
00:25:24,793 --> 00:25:26,399
Yeah, I see now.

544
00:25:26,892 --> 00:25:29,974
I guess I should just probably be
a better person. Thanks.

545
00:25:30,027 --> 00:25:34,278
"Therefore if thine enemy
hunger, feed him."

546
00:25:35,149 --> 00:25:36,172
If he thirst,

547
00:25:36,287 --> 00:25:37,484
give him drink.

548
00:25:37,717 --> 00:25:39,274
"Be not overcome of evil,

549
00:25:39,939 --> 00:25:42,472
but overcome evil with good."

550
00:25:43,566 --> 00:25:45,809
That might be something
for you to think about.

551
00:26:14,382 --> 00:26:16,484
Man, I practically peed
myself waiting on you.

552
00:26:16,537 --> 00:26:17,190
Where have you been?

553
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:20,245
Nowhere. But if god asks,
I was with you.

554
00:26:21,701 --> 00:26:22,841
Are you sure Rashard is gonna be here?

555
00:26:23,138 --> 00:26:24,493
I heard him talking in the limo.

556
00:26:24,937 --> 00:26:27,800
This frat party thing was at
the top of his to-do list.

557
00:26:28,083 --> 00:26:29,459
All we've got to do is blend in,

558
00:26:30,178 --> 00:26:31,083
ease through the door,

559
00:26:31,162 --> 00:26:32,340
and get you a moment alone with him.

560
00:26:32,393 --> 00:26:33,350
So just hold it in.

561
00:26:34,534 --> 00:26:36,189
What fraternity did you say this was?

562
00:26:36,526 --> 00:26:37,876
Alpha Rho something.

563
00:26:38,427 --> 00:26:39,456
Alpha Rho Nu?

564
00:26:39,938 --> 00:26:40,984
A black fraternity?

565
00:26:45,497 --> 00:26:46,827
Part of us isn't blending in.

566
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:49,614
I'll just...
I'll be in the car, okay?

567
00:26:52,104 --> 00:26:54,044
<i>[Namie Amuro - "Shine More!"]
English version, written by Sandra Pires</i>

568
00:27:08,406 --> 00:27:08,964
Rashard.

569
00:27:09,075 --> 00:27:09,603
Rashard.

570
00:27:11,047 --> 00:27:11,994
Can I talk to you?

571
00:27:14,053 --> 00:27:15,468
Yo, excuse me a sec, man.

572
00:27:15,721 --> 00:27:16,383
Let's go.

573
00:27:19,119 --> 00:27:20,247
What are you doing here, man?

574
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:21,602
You know what I'm doing here.

575
00:27:21,797 --> 00:27:23,927
Look, I'm just as freaked out
about what happened as you,

576
00:27:24,230 --> 00:27:26,544
but there was a right thing
to do and a wrong thing to do.

577
00:27:26,775 --> 00:27:28,300
And we picked wrong.

578
00:27:28,337 --> 00:27:30,262
It was an accident, man.
End of story.

579
00:27:30,313 --> 00:27:31,062
End of story?

580
00:27:31,542 --> 00:27:33,652
Your uncle is about
to have me thrown in jail, man.

581
00:27:34,185 --> 00:27:35,606
Yeah,
it was an accident,

582
00:27:35,691 --> 00:27:38,189
but the truth is the truth
and you can't just walk away from that.

583
00:27:39,225 --> 00:27:40,592
I'm telling you this
as your friend, Rashard.

584
00:27:41,026 --> 00:27:42,662
I mean, we were friends,
right?

585
00:27:42,981 --> 00:27:43,754
Yeah.

586
00:27:44,264 --> 00:27:45,673
I mean,
that's what I thought.

587
00:27:45,860 --> 00:27:47,297
Right,
so can't we fig...

588
00:27:47,348 --> 00:27:49,499
but then you got to try
to rat me out like that?

589
00:27:50,247 --> 00:27:52,736
- Man, I don't even know...
- What? Rashard, it's not like that.

590
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:55,247
No? Okay, then what is it like, huh?

591
00:27:55,881 --> 00:27:57,547
You know how hard I worked for this.

592
00:27:58,094 --> 00:27:59,361
You know how much I got on the line?

593
00:27:59,413 --> 00:28:02,075
$50 million over the first 5 years,
if I read it right.

594
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:04,546
But I came to talk to you, man,
not your uncle.

595
00:28:04,598 --> 00:28:06,013
Man, this is me, man!

596
00:28:07,214 --> 00:28:10,087
Yo, and if you want
to mess with me, bring it on.

597
00:28:10,824 --> 00:28:13,876
'Cause I'll hit you back
50 million times harder.

598
00:28:15,176 --> 00:28:16,382
Why don't you just go home, man?

599
00:28:16,939 --> 00:28:17,867
Get out of my life.

600
00:28:33,694 --> 00:28:34,118
Wallace?

601
00:28:34,227 --> 00:28:35,023
What are you doing here?

602
00:28:35,267 --> 00:28:37,061
I'm at a party.
What does it look like?

603
00:28:38,191 --> 00:28:38,933
What's wrong?

604
00:28:39,035 --> 00:28:40,346
Stay away from this guy, seriously.

605
00:28:40,964 --> 00:28:41,628
What?

606
00:28:42,833 --> 00:28:43,717
Yo, you know this guy?

607
00:28:43,768 --> 00:28:44,679
Yeah, she knows me.

608
00:28:44,763 --> 00:28:46,557
She knows me well enough
to take my word and go.

609
00:28:46,982 --> 00:28:49,696
God, Wallace, when did who I talk to
at a party become your business?

610
00:28:50,174 --> 00:28:51,578
Come on.
Jackie, let's just go.

611
00:28:51,630 --> 00:28:52,648
So what? You own me?

612
00:28:53,031 --> 00:28:55,712
It would've been nice if you returned
one of my phone calls

613
00:28:55,764 --> 00:28:56,784
when you were
in chicago,

614
00:28:57,122 --> 00:28:58,841
filled me in on this new development.

615
00:28:58,842 --> 00:29:01,613
Hey, Jackie,
is this guy bothering you?

616
00:29:02,248 --> 00:29:03,520
Yes,
he's starting to.

617
00:29:03,768 --> 00:29:05,664
Okay. Hey.

618
00:29:06,311 --> 00:29:08,342
Hey, we got a party foul over here.

619
00:29:09,859 --> 00:29:13,102
This little man here is messing
with my special lady friend.

620
00:29:14,505 --> 00:29:15,681
Hey, man.
Watch out!

621
00:29:15,734 --> 00:29:17,950
Hey, come on, man.
You don't even...

622
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:21,425
Now, how about
we enjoy this party, huh?

623
00:29:22,562 --> 00:29:25,189
This party is kind of over for me.
You know what?

624
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:28,350
I do know a really
good club in hollywood.

625
00:29:29,158 --> 00:29:31,444
We could have a really good time.

626
00:29:31,529 --> 00:29:34,568
Yeah, well, my uncle told me

627
00:29:34,621 --> 00:29:36,387
I got to stick around here
for awhile, and just...

628
00:29:36,388 --> 00:29:39,933
Oh, is he here?
Maybe I can ask for his permission.

629
00:29:39,934 --> 00:29:40,674
Okay.

630
00:29:47,858 --> 00:29:49,881
You know what?
I call my own shots.

631
00:29:50,582 --> 00:29:51,519
Let's go.

632
00:30:28,422 --> 00:30:29,778
What the hell are you doing here?

633
00:30:29,779 --> 00:30:30,932
Man, I came to talk to your nephew.

634
00:30:30,982 --> 00:30:33,934
Look. He's a good boy
with a lot on his mind,

635
00:30:33,984 --> 00:30:35,696
and he doesn't need a little rat

636
00:30:35,749 --> 00:30:37,835
like you messing with his head.

637
00:30:38,495 --> 00:30:40,869
You want to talk to someone,
you talk to me.

638
00:30:41,390 --> 00:30:43,360
Better yet,
you just keep your mouth shut.

639
00:30:44,224 --> 00:30:46,071
You see what happens when you open it.

640
00:30:47,509 --> 00:30:48,606
Now, where is he?

641
00:30:48,817 --> 00:30:50,946
Well, apparently,
he left with my ex-girlfriend.

642
00:30:51,185 --> 00:30:53,345
But you're right, uncle Monte,
he is a good boy.

643
00:30:55,005 --> 00:30:56,304
Where is she taking him?

644
00:30:57,792 --> 00:30:59,405
You know,
this might actually be fun.

645
00:30:59,867 --> 00:31:01,151
I know where she likes to go.

646
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:31,799
Place all metal objects here.

647
00:31:42,702 --> 00:31:43,672
Have a good time.

648
00:31:49,854 --> 00:31:50,465
Great.

649
00:31:51,446 --> 00:31:52,625
Thanks, deputy.

650
00:31:52,689 --> 00:31:53,470
No problem.

651
00:31:53,669 --> 00:31:55,173
Are you sure you don't
want to stay awhile,

652
00:31:55,228 --> 00:31:56,220
get a little crazy?

653
00:31:56,473 --> 00:31:57,476
Sorry.

654
00:31:57,676 --> 00:31:59,062
I have to get to church.

655
00:32:13,337 --> 00:32:15,033
It's always an uncomfortable moment,

656
00:32:15,034 --> 00:32:17,942
seeing the facade come off
a supposedly good person.

657
00:32:18,180 --> 00:32:21,608
For instance, seeing the priest
who quoted you Romans 12:19

658
00:32:21,669 --> 00:32:25,410
in a rather pleasant voice distributing
drugs to his crime lord brother

659
00:32:25,476 --> 00:32:26,364
through the confessional.

660
00:32:28,138 --> 00:32:30,631
Wait...
where's the distributing?

661
00:32:31,101 --> 00:32:32,933
There's supposed to be distributing.

662
00:32:37,615 --> 00:32:39,149
First you make me come in early,

663
00:32:39,222 --> 00:32:41,296
which is something I never do,
and then you're late.

664
00:32:42,305 --> 00:32:44,092
Fortunately,
I found this video online.

665
00:32:44,093 --> 00:32:46,323
This guy gets his whole head
stuck up an elephant's...

666
00:32:46,324 --> 00:32:47,814
Fascinating,
I'm sure,

667
00:32:48,153 --> 00:32:49,819
but I think you'd rather see this.

668
00:32:51,297 --> 00:32:54,573
So, father Patrick...
Scary-looking? Yes.

669
00:32:54,574 --> 00:32:56,676
Evil? No.

670
00:32:57,166 --> 00:32:58,929
Brother Liam,
on the other hand...

671
00:32:59,058 --> 00:33:01,035
I had to watch it twice
to get how they worked it

672
00:33:01,111 --> 00:33:02,578
but keep your eye on Liam's hymnal.

673
00:33:05,637 --> 00:33:07,891
So, the Lord giveth...

674
00:33:11,998 --> 00:33:14,163
and the stooge taketh away.

675
00:33:16,619 --> 00:33:17,619
Thumper.

676
00:33:25,407 --> 00:33:26,729
Why don't you call for pizza?

677
00:33:29,202 --> 00:33:29,830
Is this...?

678
00:33:29,968 --> 00:33:31,564
Uncle monte rucker's super phone

679
00:33:31,617 --> 00:33:34,525
in which his entire universe of
information is stored?

680
00:33:34,791 --> 00:33:35,644
Yes.

681
00:33:35,860 --> 00:33:37,823
If he's paying off Guy Abrutti,

682
00:33:37,883 --> 00:33:39,372
there's got to be
a number in there somewhere.

683
00:33:39,700 --> 00:33:41,361
The call log goes back four days.

684
00:33:41,362 --> 00:33:44,458
Just e-mail all the numbers to your dad
and let the police work ensue.

685
00:33:45,405 --> 00:33:47,436
Damn.
Up high, V. Mars.

686
00:33:48,896 --> 00:33:49,592
Hey.

687
00:33:52,395 --> 00:33:53,298
What?

688
00:33:55,216 --> 00:33:56,623
Don't I get some?

689
00:34:02,824 --> 00:34:03,934
How'd I do?

690
00:34:04,275 --> 00:34:05,636
From what I heard,

691
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:07,320
ice bitch.

692
00:34:07,372 --> 00:34:08,702
Oh, yeah, she was good.

693
00:34:08,971 --> 00:34:10,071
Poor Rashard.

694
00:34:10,072 --> 00:34:11,335
The kid never had a chance.

695
00:34:11,819 --> 00:34:14,759
It's a dubious talent, but snagging
guys has always been a breeze.

696
00:34:15,793 --> 00:34:17,746
It's holding onto
the good ones that's tricky.

697
00:34:20,324 --> 00:34:22,896
So, what do you think, Wallace?
Are you maybe free this weekend?

698
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:24,096
Hey, Wallace.

699
00:34:26,001 --> 00:34:27,889
Are we still on for
tomorrow after the game?

700
00:34:28,160 --> 00:34:29,316
Oh, yes, ma'am.

701
00:34:38,571 --> 00:34:40,686
If I could control him,
I would.

702
00:34:59,099 --> 00:35:01,041
Weevil,
what's up, man?

703
00:35:03,043 --> 00:35:03,995
Here's what's up.

704
00:35:05,536 --> 00:35:06,882
There's a traitor amongst us,

705
00:35:08,554 --> 00:35:10,877
someone who signed up
with the Fitzpatricks

706
00:35:11,164 --> 00:35:13,039
to deal drugs and break the rules.

707
00:35:14,077 --> 00:35:16,126
And I don't like it
when people break the rules.

708
00:35:17,206 --> 00:35:18,682
Do I, Thumper?

709
00:35:20,554 --> 00:35:21,678
You got anything to say?

710
00:35:22,353 --> 00:35:24,799
Yeah... so what?

711
00:35:25,848 --> 00:35:29,084
So what if we want to make some money
selling dope to rich white boys?

712
00:35:29,363 --> 00:35:30,640
Is that such a bad thing?

713
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:32,512
I don't think so.

714
00:35:33,697 --> 00:35:34,912
What do you mean, "we"?

715
00:35:35,595 --> 00:35:37,026
Do you got a mouse in your pocket?

716
00:35:37,378 --> 00:35:39,070
I mean "we," like the rest of us.

717
00:35:45,571 --> 00:35:46,832
Right.

718
00:35:48,636 --> 00:35:52,202
The Fitzpatricks made
Felix's brother disappear!

719
00:35:52,850 --> 00:35:54,500
The Reaper, your own leader!

720
00:35:55,548 --> 00:35:57,426
And now you want to go work for them?!

721
00:35:58,967 --> 00:36:00,592
Let me make sure I got this straight.

722
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:02,332
Working with our enemies.

723
00:36:02,333 --> 00:36:03,447
You've got a problem with that?

724
00:36:03,498 --> 00:36:04,505
You bet I do.

725
00:36:04,547 --> 00:36:06,332
Then you can tell us
what you were doing

726
00:36:06,377 --> 00:36:08,807
meeting at the Neptune Grand with
Logan Echolls!

727
00:36:10,570 --> 00:36:13,631
And you were gonna bust me up
for selling to an 09er last week.

728
00:36:14,118 --> 00:36:15,954
Hector's cousin works
maintenance there.

729
00:36:17,245 --> 00:36:18,140
He saw you.

730
00:36:18,407 --> 00:36:21,374
all buddy-buddy with
the piece of trash who killed Felix.

731
00:36:22,278 --> 00:36:23,490
You're right,
there's rules,

732
00:36:23,751 --> 00:36:25,358
like not selling out your brothers.

733
00:36:26,239 --> 00:36:27,770
I'm not like you,
Weevil.

734
00:36:28,036 --> 00:36:29,262
I don't make good speeches,

735
00:36:30,167 --> 00:36:31,880
so I'm just gonna say, "adios."

736
00:36:32,881 --> 00:36:34,186
I hope that covers it.

737
00:36:35,618 --> 00:36:36,882
Hey, hold on, man.

738
00:36:45,517 --> 00:36:47,078
That's enough.
Let's get out of here.

739
00:37:05,096 --> 00:37:07,860
Take Weevil's bike,
drive it into the ocean.

740
00:37:08,076 --> 00:37:09,779
I'll pick you up and bring you back.

741
00:37:21,391 --> 00:37:23,975
You lied all along,
didn't you?

742
00:37:24,672 --> 00:37:26,636
That night on the bridge,
you were there.

743
00:37:27,060 --> 00:37:28,779
You killed felix,
didn't you?!

744
00:37:29,644 --> 00:37:31,818
That's an interesting theory,
Eli.

745
00:37:32,252 --> 00:37:34,442
But before you think
about spreading it around,

746
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:36,745
I think you should see something.

747
00:37:38,373 --> 00:37:39,326
Remember this?

748
00:37:42,043 --> 00:37:44,034
That night you nearly
kicked Curly's head in?

749
00:37:44,979 --> 00:37:46,257
So I'd keep my mouth shut...

750
00:37:46,541 --> 00:37:48,726
'cause you probably don't want
this getting around to, say...

751
00:37:48,829 --> 00:37:49,891
... the cops, do you?

752
00:37:51,371 --> 00:37:52,328
I didn't think so.

753
00:38:00,420 --> 00:38:01,329
